{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Wduz5EVKviGEz3kr12tKqR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Let me write the F25 plan.\n\nKey observations:\n1. All F1–F24 are done (sentinel files exist)\n2. F13 built `GET /api/users` with search and cursor pagination (in `src/lib/users.ts`)\n3. F14 built `GET /api/users/[id]` for user profiles\n4. The `/users` page currently has just a stub with \"Users\" heading\n\n\n5. The `/users/[id]` page doesn't exist yet, but `IdentityChip` already links to it\n6. F25 is about building the search page itself—a search input that queries `/api/users?q=...` and displays clickable results that navigate to individual user profiles\n7. The API is already built, so I just need the frontend\n\nI'll create a `useUserSearch` hook to manage the search state and API calls, then update the users page to be a client component with a search input and results list showing resolved_id, first_seen, last_seen, and event_count.\n\nI need to handle clicking a result to navigate to the user detail page, implement cursor-based pagination with a load more button, show an empty state when there are no results, and display a loading indicator while fetching.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4035,"cache_read_input_tokens":45677,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4035,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d7adcc68-1c43-467b-b3ed-58aad5dfe1a9","uuid":"844d6276-a9fb-45d8-b26d-6a822d1ec4e8"}
